      "body_md": "**Linux Security Lite 1.0.3** — the standalone, Linux-only security-audit tool in the AuditToolkit suite. First 1.0.3 baseline after full functional + UI alignment review.\n\n### Three Linux packages\n| Package | Distributions |\n| --- | --- |\n| `.deb` | Debian, Ubuntu and derivatives |\n| `.rpm` (noarch) | RHEL, Fedora, AlmaLinux, Rocky, CentOS Stream, openSUSE/SLES, Amazon Linux |\n| `.tar.gz` | Any other Linux distribution (generic/offline) |\n\nAll three bundle an offline Python wheelhouse and are served by the `audittoolkit-linux-security-lite-web` systemd service on `127.0.0.1:8089`.\n\n### Highlights\n- Web console re-engineered to the suite left-nav shell (dark, left menu + right detail) with a matching dark login\n- Documentation reader aligned to the central customer-docs model (docs repo -> Control Centre)\n- Documentation Centre now resolves EULA/License/Disclaimer; `DISCLAIMER.md` packaged in all formats\n- Versions reconciled to a single 1.0.3 baseline\n\nVerify downloads against `SHA256SUMS-1.0.3.txt`. See `README.md` for install commands and `CHANGELOG.md` for the full change list.",
